Mark Cavendish of the U.K. Wins 15th Stage of Cycling’s Tour de France

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-07-17T15:22:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-17/mark-cavendish-of-the-u-k-wins-15th-stage-of-cycling-s-tour-de-france.html
Mark Cavendish  of the U.K. won the
15th stage of cycling’s Tour de  France , a 192.5 kilometer (119-
mile) trip from Limoux to Montpellier in southern France.  It was his fourth stage win on the Tour this year and the
19th of his career.  Thomas Voeckler  of France keeps the race leader’s yellow
jersey.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at  at
 celser@bloomberg.net  